      <h1 class='title'>Honours System</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 16 July 2004 vol 663 c69WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_69ws' title='Col. 69WS &mdash; HL Deb 16 July 2004 vol 663 c69WS' name='column_69ws' href='#column_69ws' rel='bookmark'>69WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S5LV0663P0_20040716_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-valerie-amos' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040716_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Ms Valerie Amos' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-valerie-amos" title="Ms Valerie Amos">The Lord President of the Council (Baroness Amos):</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para"> My right honourable friend the Prime Minister has made the following Ministerial Statement.</p><p>The Government have received Sir Hayden Phillips's report on his review of the honours system. Copies have been placed in the Libraries of the House.</p><p>We shall consider this report alongside the report <span class="italic">A Matter of Honour: Reforming the Honours System</span> (HC212) by the Public Administration Select Committee which was published on 7 July. The Government will make a Statement on the way forward later this year.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
